                            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #444;">Website Login Sessions</td>
                            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #444;">7 days</td>
                            <td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #444;">On logout, or automatically after 7 days</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>

                <p>
                    <strong>Important:</strong> You can request deletion of your data at any time (see "Your Privacy Rights" below). However, if you continue to use the Bot after deletion, we will collect the minimum data needed to provide Bot functionality again. If you want permanent deletion, please stop using the Bot after requesting data removal.
                </p>

                <h3>Your Privacy Rights</h3>
                <p>You have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Right to Access:</strong> You can request to see what data we have about you</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Deletion:</strong> You can request that we delete your data (also known as the "right to be forgotten")</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Correction:</strong> You can request that we correct any inaccurate data we have about you</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Data Portability:</strong> You can request to receive your data in a commonly used, machine-readable format</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Restriction:</strong> You can request that we limit how we process your data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> You can object to certain types of data processing</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Non-Discrimination:</strong> You will not be treated differently for exercising your privacy rights</li>
                </ul>

                <p>
                    <strong>We Never Sell Your Data:</strong> Your personal information is never sold to third parties, and we do not share it for marketing purposes.
                </p>

                <p>
                    <strong>For EU Users:</strong> Under GDPR, you have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection supervisory authority if you believe your rights have been violated.
                </p>

                <p>
                    To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the methods listed in the "Contact Us" section below.
                </p>

                <h3>Data Security</h3>
                <p>
                    Your data is stored in a secured database to prevent unauthorized access. We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
                </p>
                <p>
                    However, no method of electronic storage or transmission over the internet is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your data, we cannot guarantee absolute security. In the event of an unauthorized data breach, we will notify affected users through the Discord client application.
                </p>

                <h3>Third-Party Services</h3>
                <p>The Bot interacts with the following third-party services:</p>

                <h4>EA Game API</h4>
                <p>
                    We fetch your public Star Wars Galaxy of Heroes game data directly from EA's servers using the ally codes you provide. Your Discord user ID and other Discord-related information is <strong>not shared</strong> with EA. Only your ally code is used to retrieve publicly available game data.
                </p>

                <h4>Patreon API</h4>
                <p>
                    For premium subscribers, we fetch subscription information from the Patreon API to verify your subscription status. This is limited to your Patreon ID and Discord ID. Patreon handles all payment processing—we do not receive or store your credit card or payment information.
                </p>

                <h4>Discord OAuth2</h4>
                <p>
                    The SWGoHBot website offers optional login via Discord's OAuth2 service. When you log in, your browser is redirected to Discord's authorization page, and Discord returns your basic profile information to us: your Discord user ID, username, and avatar. We use this solely to identify you on the website and provide access to configuration features. Your Discord credentials (password) are never shared with or visible to us.
                </p>

                <h4>This Website</h4>
                <p>
                    When you log in to the SWGoHBot website, we set a session cookie to keep you signed in. This cookie is stored in your browser and links to a session record in our database containing your Discord user ID, username, and avatar. Sessions expire after 7 days or immediately on logout. If you do not log in, no cookies are set and no data is collected by the website.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The website does not use tracking pixels or third-party analytics services.
                </p>

                <h3>Changes to This Policy</h3>
                <p>
                    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technology, legal requirements, or other factors. When we make significant changes, we will notify users through an announcement in our support Discord server.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy indicates when it was last revised. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your information.
                </p>

                <h3>Contact Us</h3>
